name: Il Totem Misterioso
La Roccia Parlante

description: From the pages of writer Robert E. Howard comes the debut of Dynamite's Thulsa Doom! Written by Kull writer Arvid Nelson and illustrated by Lui (Red Sonja) Antonio, the opening story arc also features cover artist Alex Ross! Featuring the origins of the ultimate anti-hero, Thulsa Doom #1 opens after the destruction of Atlantis, when the world was in chaos and Thulsa sought his own path to ultimate power!
name: Feast of Venom, Issue One: Who Will Cry For Atlantis?

description: With the death of Solomon Grundy, Cyrus has no distractions or lies to hide behind anymore. We finally learn the answer to who killed Cyrus Gold and why. But will Cyrus forgive his killer and end his curse forever? And with his past mistakes, will Hell let him go? Time runs out for Cyrus as Blackest Night hits. Is this the end of Solomon Grundy?
name: Buried On A Sunday!

description:
When Superman's greatest foes leave their native Metropolis and join Chicago's notorious criminal organization, the Vicious Ciricle, the call is put out for the Man of Steel to save the day.

But the Dragon ain't exactly doing back flips when he's forced to ally himself with a guy who wears his underwear on the outside of the pants.
name: Chicago

description: Both Superman and the Savage Dragon were attacked and left with no memory who attacked them. They must team up to find out who attacked them. Superman and Savage Dragon would have to go to Apokolips to find out why Superman had no memory.
name: Metropolis
Pirates Revenge ; City from Outer Space

description: They’re back! What happened Spider-Man, Colonel America, Power Man, Giant-Man and Wolverine at the end of MARVEL ZOMBIES 2? Where were they transported to...and, more importantly, when? A frightening five-part weekly event shambles to life here, penned by resident (evil) MARVEL ZOMBIES 3 and 4 scribe Fred Van Lente and three of today’s hottest novelists of zombie fiction! In this first chapter, your friendly neighborhood undead arachnid arrives in the swingin’ college days of his distant past, and when the Sinister Six threaten his loved ones, he seizes the opportunity to undo all the horror he's caused as a flesh-eating freak. But can a monster truly become a hero, no matter how guilt-ridden he is? Or will he learn the hard way that with great hunger also comes…great hunger?
name: With Great Hunger, There Must Also Come Great Hunger!

description: Test TEST

The Phantasm from the animated film BATMAN: THE MASK OF THE PHANTASM returns! While Batman's off spying on Gotham's mobsters, it's up to Batgirl to face the deadly Phantasm on her own!

1. A Bat in the House (written by Dan Slott)

2. The First Time (written by Ty Templeton)
name: A Bat in the House ; The First Time

description: Batman learns that appearances can be deceiving in Moscow in part 3 of this 5-part story! Every mobster in Russia seems too terrified of the Tsar and his Bear to talk about the crime kingpin. But is Bear having doubts about his mission and his boss? Who can Batman trust in this unfamiliar city where nothing is as it seems?
name: The Bat and the Beast, Part Three

description: At age 22, Yenny longs for a career as a catwalk supermodel. Yes, she's gorgeous, but two things stand in her way, monumentally huge feet! So instead of an apartment in Paris, her home is a cottage on Puerto Rico's Villa Los Kubos beach, which she shares with her globe-trotting mother Yunissa, her irrepressibly mischievous iguana sidekick Zacha, and a tiny, silent sea turtle named Bukestalifaro, "Buke" to friends. Between modeling assignments and long stretches of beach-lolling and volleyball, Yenny tackles an assortment of extremely odd jobs, most notably that of babysitter to the nightmare child Cheecaca. Surrounded by an assortment of outlandish neighbors and family, Yenny and Zacha manage to bring cheerful chaos and confusion to their lovely corner of the world on a daily basis.
Yenny's problem with Zacha the iguana are larger than her feet! Will this poor girl survive the constant torments of this crazy lizard?

Yenny and all the gang are off to Sidny World, the happiest place this side of the earth. Join us this month as Zacha crash tests every ride available, Kelso falls in love with Yenny, and Yunissa complains about her ex-husband in every corner.

WEDNESDAY COMICS, DC's new, 12-issue weekly series, reaches its incredible conclusion in September. Here are just some of the highlights of this third and final month:

In BATMAN, WEDNESDAY COMICS' weekly cover feature, Bruce Wayne digs further into a steamy murder mystery. It's a classic noir tale by the Eisner Award-winning 100 BULLETS team of writer Brian Azzarello and artist Eduardo Risso.

METAMORPHO dives into a fever-dream of an adventure, written by New York Times best-selling writer Neil Gaiman with art by Eisner Award-winner Michael Allred (Madman).

THE DEMON AND CATWOMAN make a deadly detour after Selina Kyle attempts to rob Jason Blood's collection of antiquities, taking her into unexpected territory. Written by Walter Simonson (Thor, MANHUNTER) with art by famed DC cover artist Brian Stelfreeze.

DEADMAN is warned off of pursuing a serial killer by the only being who could do so: Rama Kushna. It's a tale of mystery and mystics written by Dave Bullock and Vinton Heuck, art by Dave Bullock.

KAMANDI explores the living nightmare that is the world after the Great Disaster in a sprawling tale written by Dave Gibbons (WATCHMEN, GREEN LANTERN CORPS) with art by Ryan Sook (Buffy The Vampire Slayer, ARKHAM ASYLUM: LIVING HELL).

The feathers fly as HAWKMAN heads into slam-bang action, as written and illustrated by Kyle Baker (PLASTIC MAN, Special Forces).

SGT. ROCK is captured by German forces - but will the Rock break? Find out in a gritty wartime epic written by Adam Kubert (SUPERMAN: LAST SON) and ilustrated by legendary comics artist Joe Kubert.

And don't miss these continuing features:

THE METAL MEN, written by Dan DiDio with art by Jose Luis Garcia-Lopez.

THE FLASH, written by Karl Kerschl (TEEN TITANS YEAR ONE, THE FLASH: THE FASTEST MAN ALIVE) and Brenden Fletcher with art by Karl Kerschl.

SUPERGIRL, written by Jimmy Palmiotti (JONAH HEX) with art by Amanda Conner (POWER GIRL).

GREEN LANTERN, written by Kurt Busiek (TRINITY, ASTRO CITY) with art by Joe Quiñones (TEEN TITANS GO!).

SUPERMAN, written by John Arcudi (The Mask) with art by Lee Bermejo (JOKER).

ADAM STRANGE, written and illustrated by Paul Pope (BATMAN: YEAR 100).

WONDER WOMAN, written and illustrated by Ben Caldwell (Dare Detectives).

THE TEEN TITANS, written by Eddie Berganza with art by Sean Galloway.
name: 9 of 12

description: It's snowing in Puerto Rico?!? How can that be? This is a terrible thing for an island that has never seen snow... and even worse for Yenny, who simply can't stand the cold!

Science is not your friend! The Human Flame is about to learn this the hard way as he accidentally unlocks the terror behind the doors of the most secret facility at S.T.A.R. Labs. Mike's on the cusp of becoming one of the most powerful villains in the DC Universe! Or he may just be on the cusp of being horribly murdered! It's hard to tell with cusps sometimes.
name: Step Five: Come Up With An Ingenious Master Plan

description: Zacha goes crazy, exploding everything anytime she sees a firecracker! This is one "explosive" issue, and no one's safe when the iguana stands close to anything flammable!
Don't mess with cupid, because he has strange magical powers! Strange like making you get FAT! Yeah... that weird.

There's one thing that the pale gothic girls really hate, and that's sun-tanned surfers. However there's one thing pale gothic girls really like, and that's torturing sun-tanned surfers! Poor Yenny meets the Blanko Goth Girls!

Gabriel Cole's family has fallen apart, and Alpha One has a nuclear bomb! But Alpha's pride could be his undoing when Cole finds himself alone in the "hero's" headquarters...and his rage begins to lead him down a terrifying road!
name: Wide Awake

description: At age 22, Yenny longs for a career as a catwalk supermodel. Yes, she's gorgeous, but two things stand in her way: monumentally huge feet. So instead of an apartment in Paris her home is a cottage on Puerto Rico's Villa Los Kubos beach, which she shares with her globe-trotting mother Yunissa, her irrepressibly mischievous iguana sidekick Zacha, and a tiny, silent sea turtle named Bukestalifaro ("Buke" to friends).

How do you decide between love and duty? When the Companions make their way to the land of the elves, Tanis is confronted by the woman he's loved since childhood - and a choice no man should have to make! Plus - a journey into the heart of Verminaard's stronghold!
name: Part 6 of 8

volume.name: Dragonlance Chronicles; Dragons of Autumn Twilight

description: The fan-favorite adaptation reaches a fever pitch! The quest carries the companions to the catacombs beneath Pax Tharkas - can they convince the captives within the dread city to revolt against the evil of Verminaard? Can they even hope to survive the wrath of two dragons in service to Takhisis, the Queen of Darkness? And what of the traitor in their midst - Who is it?
name: Part 7 of 8

volume.name: Dragonlance Chronicles; Dragons of Autumn Twilight

description: The concluding chapter to Weis' and Hickman's epic Dragons of Autumn Twilight! As the world slides closer to violent upheaval, the Companions must battle their most dangerous enemy - Verminaard! Meanwhile, the lovers Goldmoon and Riverwind share what may be their last moments together.
name: Part 8 of 8

volume.name: Dragonlance Chronicles; Dragons of Autumn Twilight

description: Following the shocking end of “Silver Scream,” the Doctor now finds himself on trial for his life by the Shadow Proclamation! To survive, he has to prove his innocence… but the prosecution is Mister Finch from “School Reunion.”
name: Fugitive, Part 1 of 4

description: The Heroes discover the existance of Dragon Orbs used to control the Dragons. They are split into two parties, both in search of Dragon Orbs.
name: Dragons of Winter Night (Part 1 of 4)

volume.name: Dragonlance Chronicles: Dragons of Winter Night

description: The Companions are torn asunder as one of them embarks upon a suicidal quest! And with Krynn dividing into warring factions, The Companions; only real allies have become deadly enemies!
name: Dragons of Winter Night (Part 2 of 4)

volume.name: Dragonlance Chronicles: Dragons of Winter Night

description: As Sturm Brightblade is forced to choose between the Order he reveres and the friends he loves, the lovers are torn between duty and passion, and the Companions journey to the most revered spot in all of Krynn: the Tomb of Huma! The secret concealed there will stagger them, and perhaps, bestow them a priceless gift!
name: Dragons of Winter Night (Part 3 of 4)

volume.name: Dragonlance Chronicles: Dragons of Winter Night

description: Secrets will be revealed. A hero will make the ultimate sacrifice. And the friendship of the Companions will be tested as never before!
name: Dragons of Winter Night (Part 4 of 4)

volume.name: Dragonlance Chronicles: Dragons of Winter Night

description: The beginning of the Chronicles Trilogy as a band of heroes set out first to find evidence of the long lost Gods of Krynn and reveal the return of an ancient evil.
name: Dragons of Spring Dawning (Part 1 of 12)

volume.name: Dragonlance Chronicles; Dragons of Spring Dawning
Dragonlance Chronicles; Dragons of Spring Dawning
Dragonlance Chronicles; Dragons of Spring Dawning
Dragonlance Chronicles; Dragons of Spring Dawning
Dragonlance Chronicles; Dragons of Spring Dawning

description: Caramon and Raistlin may be brothers, but Raistlin's lust for power has ever kept them from truly boding. Now, with the world crumbling around them, can the twins come to terms with each other? At long last, learn the secret of Raistlin's trial of sorcery!
name: Dragons of Spring Dawning (Part 6 of 12)

volume.name: Dragonlance Chronicles; Dragons of Spring Dawning

description: As the War for Krynn escalates to undreamed levels, the mysterious mage Fizban returns! But is he an ally - or an unstable element that could destroy the last remnants of hope? Meanwhile, the Companions embark on their most dangerous mission yet: to penetrate the Dark Queen's stronghold in Neraka!
name: Dragons of Spring Dawning (Part 7 of 12)

volume.name: Dragonlance Chronicles; Dragons of Spring Dawning

description: The Companions are led by Fizban to the hallowed grove called Godshome, but along the way a terrible loss is suffered. A loss that tears their hearts apart! Plus, the origin of the Green Gemstone Man is finally revealed!
name: Dragons of Spring Dawning (Part 8 of 12)

volume.name: Dragonlance Chronicles; Dragons of Spring Dawning

description: There were times that they thought they'd not survive the journey, but the Companions finally arrive in the Dark Queen's stronghold in Neraka - only to face perils greater than they faced in their travels! And to save Laurana, Tanis surrenders himself to Kitiara! Can his submissions save the lives of the friends he has come to love?
name: Dragons of Spring Dawning (Part 9 of 12)

volume.name: Dragonlance Chronicles; Dragons of Spring Dawning

description: A number of the Companions are taken captive by the dragonarmy. Can Caramon, Tax, and Tika find a way to escape the order of death that hangs over them? Will they survive the arrival of Takhisis, the dark queen responsible for the war they're fighting?
name: Dragons of Spring Dawning (Part 10 of 12)

volume.name: Dragonlance Chronicles; Dragons of Spring Dawning

description: The Crown of Power has a torrid history of good and evil! Now with it being completely corrupt, can even Tanis' soul withstand the pull of its' power? Meanwhile, is another Companion giving in to evil? Has Raistlin's soul gone as black as his mage robes?
name: Dragons of Spring Dawning (Part 11 of 12)

volume.name: Dragonlance Chronicles; Dragons of Spring Dawning

description: This is it! The final chapter in the epic trilogy! As the war against the forces of evil rages on, is there any hope of survival for any of the Companions? Will Raistlin give in to the temptation of the power he holds or will he stand next to his friends in their final battle?
name: Dragons of Spring Dawning (Part 12 of 12)

volume.name: Dragonlance Chronicles; Dragons of Spring Dawning

description: The Julia arc concludes with a cold-blooded murder. Queen Victoria would have censored this issue.
name: Julia Conclusion

description: Knights of the Dinner Table is a multiple award-winning periodical featuring the gaming industry's most popular comic strip, as well as being a full-fledged gaming magazine. That's right, more than half of each issue is devoted to reviews, adventure ideas and tips, maps, monsters, NPCs, magic items, and many other articles for a wide variety of games and game systems, written from a gamer's perspective. A hilarious and hysterical slice of (fantasy) life in strips, features and a wonderful celebration of the gaming culture!

Adopted daughter and principal collaborator of James Fitzroy, roving ambassador and special correspondent for the American Secretary of State in Europe, Susan is a clever, multilingual young woman, in full bloom and perfectly happy in the eyes of an attentive father. But this too-perfect happiness hides many faults, sorrows, and mysteries. Trapped by her past, Susan will have to play her most dangerous role in a life already rich with adventure as 'Lady S.,' high-class spy in a diplomatic environment where the stakes are higher than she could dare imagine!
name: Here's To Suzie
